import numpy as np
from PIL import Image, ImageDraw
import math

def draw_tree(draw, x, y, length, angle, depth):
    if depth > 0:
        # Calculate end point
        x2 = x + int(math.cos(math.radians(angle)) * length)
        y2 = y - int(math.sin(math.radians(angle)) * length)
        
        # Draw the branch
        draw.line([(x, y), (x2, y2)], fill=(101, 67, 33), width=max(1, depth))
        
        # Recursive calls for branches
        draw_tree(draw, x2, y2, length * 0.7, angle - 30, depth - 1)
        draw_tree(draw, x2, y2, length * 0.7, angle + 30, depth - 1)

# Create a blank white image
width = 400
height = 400
image = Image.new('RGB', (width, height), 'white')
draw = ImageDraw.Draw(image)

# Start drawing the tree from the bottom center
start_x = width // 2
start_y = height - 50
start_length = 100
start_angle = 90
depth = 9

draw_tree(draw, start_x, start_y, start_length, start_angle, depth)

# Save the image
image.save("tree_fractal.png")
image

import numpy as np
from PIL import Image, ImageDraw, ImageFont
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Create a blank image
width = 100
height = 100
image = Image.new('RGB', (width, height), 'white')
draw = ImageDraw.Draw(image)

# Draw a heart shape
def draw_heart(draw, x, y, size):
    # Heart shape coordinates
    left_curve = [(x, y-2), (x-2, y-1), (x-3, y), (x-3, y+1), (x-2, y+2), (x, y+3)]
    right_curve = [(x, y-2), (x+2, y-1), (x+3, y), (x+3, y+1), (x+2, y+2), (x, y+3)]
    
    # Draw curves
    draw.line(left_curve, fill='red', width=2)
    draw.line(right_curve, fill='red', width=2)
    
    # Add text
    font = ImageFont.load_default()
    draw.text((x-3, y), 'A', fill='red', font=font)

# Draw heart in center of image
center_x = width // 2
center_y = height // 2
draw_heart(draw, center_x, center_y, 20)

# Save and display the image
image.save("heart_with_a.png")
image
